  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6876",
  "title": "Hydratation problem with react-instantsearch-nextjs and 2 InstantSearchNext components in the same page",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nMaybe I'm doing it wrong, but I need to have multiple instance of instant search in a page, with different configuration, using the same index.\n\nTo reproduce, I took the next js app and changing it to only display 2 boxes, one displaying 4 Apple products, and one displaying 4 Hp products.\n\n<img width=\"500\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5c0588d9-397f-44ed-8a2e-ecfb654a2fed\" />\n\nas you can see there is an error, it's an hydration error.\n\nlooking at the generated html, I can see 2 different objects attached to the same window property, I suspect it's the problem.\n\n<img width=\"712\" height=\"147\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/14222b40-59e9-4e74-a497-dbc6f2b2bccf\" />\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Use the sandbox preview url https://lysjwf-3000.csb.app/\n2. observe the flickering on the top set of results\n3. look at nextjs issue at the bottom left\n\nrepo here https://github.com/stuff/instantsearch-nextjs-app-bug\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttps://lysjwf-3000.csb.app/\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nNo flickering, no hydration error\n\n### Package version\n\nalgoliasearch: 5.1.1, react-instantsearch: 7.22.1, react-instantsearch-nextjs: 1.0.11\n\n### Operating system\n\n_No response_\n\n### Browser\n\n_No response_\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [x] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
